narratives.question_text: How would you summarize ECON 111 01 for a fellow student? Would you recommend ECON 111 01 to another student? Why or why not?
comments: Highly recommended for any interested in the subject matter.
A good class if you're serious about learnign english and invested in theory, as well as read some really cool books

This class was a little intimidating, as this year the class was combined with graduate students, but I felt like I learned a lot and a very unique perspective on some classic as well as modern literature. I would definitely recommend it, but be prepared! The reading is a lot (a novel a week, usually pretty long), but manageable.

Solid course. Professor Dimock is great and engaging, and the subject matter is generally interesting. My only criticism is that I think he course lost some steam towards the end--I felt like the class was uninspired by a bunch of the books down the stretch. Class discussion was still interesting, but I think could be made better by looking at the reading list at the end of the course.
